name: semio
explanation: is the root package for everything in semio.

name: geometry
explanation: contains everything that is geometry related.

name: artifact
explanation: is anything that is produced by human or a computer.

name: arrangement
explanation: is a sequence of plans for scripts of the same kind.

name: choice
explanation: is one thing out of a predifined set of choices.

name: description
explanation: is describing something in an custom or unstructured way.

name: identifier
explanation: is a unique identifier to distingusish it from another artifact.

name: integer
explanation: is a number with a number without decimals.

name: layout
explanation: is a graph of sobjects (nodes) and attractions (slightly directed edges).

name: natural
explanation: is a non-negative number with no decimals.

name: sobject
explanation: is the semantic description of an object.
